I found the bug, if you take a look at my code below:

foreach (var neighbor in GetNeighbors(currentCell)
.Where(x => x.Sign != '#' && (x.Step == -1 || x.Step > currentCell.Step)))
{
	var cell = neighbor;

	while (cell.IsJumpPod)
		cell = jumps[cell];

	if (cell.IsTeleporterEntry)
        	cell = teleporters[cell.Sign];

	cell.Step = currentCell.Step + 1;
        cellQueue.Enqueue(cell);
}
I use filtering on neighbors: x.Step == -1 || x.Step > currentCell.Step
Meaning if it's not-visited (== -1) or if can be overriden by a lower value
And that's fine, but what I missed out is that neighbor after performing jumps and teleports can change to another cell, and I need to check if that cell also satisfies the condition ^^
